<div class="search-tips">
    <h3>Search tips</h3>
    <ul class="list--search-tips">
        <li>
            <dl>
                <dt class="tip-heading">Keyword Searching</dt>
                <dd>Combine keywords and attributes to find specific items.
                    <dl class="example">
                        <dt>Examples:</dt>
                        <dd><ul>
                                <li>morrison beloved</li>
                                <li>Egypt foreign relations</li>
                            </ul>
                        </dd>
                    </dl>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </li>
        <li>
            <dl>
                <dt class="tip-heading">Phrase Searching</dt>
                <dd>Use quotation marks to search as a phrase.
                    <dl class="example">
                        <dt>Examples:</dt>
                        <dd><ul>
                                <li>"free market"</li>
                                <li>"mourning becomes electra"</li>
                            </ul>
                        </dd>
                    </dl>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </li>
        <li>
            <dl>
                <dt class="tip-heading">Requiring Words and Phrases</dt>
                <dd>Use "+" before a term to make it required. (Otherwise results matching only some of your terms may be included).
                    <dl class="example">
                        <dt>Example:</dt>
                        <dd><ul>
                                <li>+cuba +politics</li>
                            </ul>
                        </dd>
                    </dl>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </li>
        <li>
            <dl>
                <dt class="tip-heading">Excluding Words or Phrases</dt>
                <dd>Use "-" before a word or phrase to exclude it.
                    <dl class="example">
                        <dt>Example:</dt>
                        <dd><ul>
                                <li>jaguar -car -automobiles</li>
                            </ul>
                        </dd>
                    </dl>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </li>
        <li>
            <dl>
                <dt class="tip-heading">Joining Queries</dt>
                <dd>Use "OR", "AND", and "NOT" to create complex boolean logic. You can use parentheses in your complex expressions. Use the <%= link_to('Guided Search', '/guided') %> or <%= link_to('Advanced Search', '/advanced') %> to join across mulitple fields.
                    <dl class="example">
                        <dt>Example:</dt>
                        <dd><ul>
                                <li>paul AND auster</li>
                            </ul>
                        </dd>
                    </dl>
                </dd>
            </dl>
        </li>
        <li>Truncation and wildcards are not supported - word-stemming is done automatically.</li>
    </ul>
</div>